Description: New Era Golf Ohio has an outstanding reputation as Central Ohio’s leader in golf course facilities.
Full Description: New Era Golf Ohio has an outstanding reputation as Central Ohio's leader in golf course facilities.  Offering first-class service, excellent playing conditions and challenging layouts, New Era Golf Clubs are always on the top of the list for players in the region.  With the recent addition of New Albany Links to their portfolio, New Era has proven they are a top golf course management firm and now offer an even better value to its members and daily-fee guests. When you visit a New Era Golf Facility you immediately know the management is there to provide the golfers with a great time from the golf course to the pro shop to the grille room.  Between all the club managers and golf professionals, New Era boasts over 250 years of golf course management experience.  Led by PGA member and managing partner, Ray Finnearty takes pride in knowing the members by name and is a usual sight around the clubs.  "I am very proud to bring together four of the top clubs in the Columbus area.  Our goal is to offer the best value and experience around and I think we're doing a good job so far.  However, we will continue to improve in all areas of our operations and look forward to a great 2014" says Finnearty. New Albany Links was added to the New Era Golf Portfolio in early January bringing the course count to four clubs.  "We have big plans for New Albany. Our immediate goal is to soften the golf course to improve the playability for golfers of all skill levels.  We will cut back the Heather Grass, remove some of the bunkers that are not in play, and widen some of the landing areas over time.   This will drastically improve the pace of play.  This is a phenomenal golf course.   "These improvements are designed to make New Albany Links more player-friendly while preserving the design of the architect" indicates Michael J. Emigh, New Era's Director of Membership. Although the New Era Membership Product improved with this addition, the cost of the membership stayed the same.  Now all New Era Members have the opportunity to play at New Albany Links, Glenross Golf Club, Royal American Links and Bent Tree Golf Club.  Each club offers a unique challenge although excellent course conditions and service will be a standard throughout the portfolio.

Description: Injury Sciences offers forensic software and services to property or casualty insurers in the United States
Full Description: Injury Sciences LLC is the leader in software and services which provide claims professionals with objective, scientific information for use in the evaluation of an auto claim. Injury Sciences’ software and services are the result of over 20 years of research and analysis of vehicular collisions and injury outcomes. Injury Sciences’ team of leading forensic scientist has conducted extensive research regarding human response to auto collision events.  Many of these studies have been published in peer-reviewed scientific publications and are internationally recognized and referenced in the scientific community.  Injury Sciences software and services are currently used by more than 50 different insurance carriers.   The company offers WrExpert, a technology that analyzes objective vehicle damage from automobile collisions, and offers detailed impact severity and injury causation evaluations; and Crash Severity Scoring, a claim triage tool that automatically scores individual repair estimates and flags. The company also offers EDR InSight that provides claims professionals a solution to facilitate the use of event data recorder (EDR) in the claims evaluation process; and EDR Triage, a claim triage tool that protects insurers from evidence spoliation by automatically identifying from repair estimate data and/or claim data when EDR data should be extracted from a vehicle during the investigation and evaluation of a claim. In addition, the company offers Photo Analytics that equips claims professionals the ability to apply crash reconstruction science directly to digital photographs taken during the claim investigation process and training solutions. Injury Sciences, LLC has a strategic alliance with ChoicePoint and Vetronix Corporation. The company is based in San Antonio, Texas. As per the transaction announced on December 14, 2012, Injury Sciences, LLC operates as a subsidiary of CCC Information Services, Inc.

Description: Random chat for college students
Headquarters Regions: Greater Seattle Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: HowRandom is an online chat site that anonymously pairs college students together in a secure environment. Offering college system email verification, San Diego-based HowRandom helps students from different schools to connect and exchange ideas. All chat information is private between the two participants, with college or university name being the only identifying characteristic. Email registration is not required to participate, however students that want their school name to be verified can enter and verify a ".edu" email address. Once verified by HowRandom, that user's school name and verified symbol act as their identity in the chats. Verification of a real college email address offers a layer of security and exclusivity and stops spammers and other similar entities from using the system. Additionally, users cannot share images or video which prevents the dissemination of inappropriate or personally identifiable information. Founded by entrepreneurs Jon Cook (Pepperdine University) and Jason Humphries (University of South Carolina), HowRandom exists to serve the college market's need for an easy way for students to meet other students that are outside of their social circle of friends and without preconceptions based on appearance or other identifiable features. Mr. Cook and Mr. Humphries previously founded Veribu, a South Carolina-based company offering a free online communication platform for performing video chats, phone calls, and text messages.

Description: PopSeal manufactures self-closing, resealable aluminum can tops especially created for the beer and soft drink industry.
Headquarters Regions: Research Triangle, East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: PopSeal® is the world’s first self-closing, resealable aluminum can top created for the beer and soft drink industry. We are setting out to revolutionize the beverage industry much like the original pop-top did almost 40 years ago. Annually, over 475 billion aluminum cans are shipped across the globe, and the industry has been unsuccessful in commercializing an all aluminum beverage can top that is both self-closing and resealable, while remaining compatible with existing manufacturing and recycling methods. Until now. PopSeal® is a US patented technology and has an expansive portfolio of pending applications in the United States and Patent Cooperation Treaty (PCT) countries. With PopSeal® technology, we can significantly reduce the carbon footprint of the beverage industry, while at the same time, provide consumers with a more environmentally friendly product that is both spill-proof and resealable.
